	"grammar": {
		"component": "Group",
		"content": [
			{
				"grammar1": {
					"component": "LO1Grammar1",
					"id": "grammar1",
					"infoTextHTML": "In this section, you'll explore how to address people politely in French. You'll learn when to use <i>Monsieur</i>, <i>Madame</i>, and <i>Mademoiselle</i>, and how to recognise their abbreviations (<i>M.</i>, <i>Mme.</i>, <i>Mlle</i>.).",
					"titleText": "1. Forms of address and politeness"
				}
			},
			{
				"grammar2": {
					"component": "LO1Grammar2",
					"id": "grammar2",
					"infoTextHTML": "Here, you'll discover when to use <i>tu</i> and <i>vous</i> to show different levels of formality. You'll practise using tu with friends, family, and children, and <i>vous</i> in formal settings or when speaking to more than one person. You'll also see how <i>toi</i> replaces <i>tu</i> in short responses like <i>Et toi ?</i>",
					"titleTextHTML": "2. The \"<i>tu</i>\" vs \"<i>vous</i>\" distinction"
				}
			}
		],
